g.text: 20 balls were rolled in the downhill direction and in
the uphill direction on approximately the same line.
The dispersion area of the 20 balls was recorded as a length and width.
Because the target of a putt is a circle, I find it convenient to express
that area as the radius of a circle enclosing that same area.
